EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to crimes; expanding the definition of “victim” for the purposes
of eligibility for compensation from the Fund for the Compensation of
Victims of Crime to include a person targeted because of certain actual
or perceived characteristics of the person; authorizing such a person to
receive compensation from the Fund for the remediation of property
owned by the person under certain circumstances; making
appropriations; and providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law authorizes certain victims of crime to receive compensation from the Fund
2 for the Compensation of Victims of Crime. (NRS 217.100, 217.260) Section 4.3 of this bill
3 expands the definition of “victim” for the purposes of eligibility for compensation from the
4 Fund to include a person targeted because of certain characteristics. Section 4.7 of this bill
5 authorizes such a victim to receive an amount not to exceed $1,000 per incident from the Fund
6 for the remediation of certain property damaged in the commission of the crime perpetrated
7 against him or her. Section 5 of this bill makes an appropriation to the: (1) Fund for the
8 purposes of providing aid to certain victims; and (2) Office of the Attorney General for the
9 purposes of providing support and resources to survivors of crimes prosecuted by the Office
10 of the Attorney General.
11 Existing law creates the Account for Victims of Human Trafficking in the State General
12 Fund and requires a recipient of an allocation of money from the Account to use the money
13 only for establishing or providing programs or services to victims of human trafficking. (NRS
14 217.530, 217.540) Section 5 makes an appropriation to the Account.
